   ---=
   In addition to changes at the affected facilities, a chart
provided by the commission indicated the changes would add 914
personnel in San Francisco, 415 in Chicago, 224 in Salt Lake City,
145 at Ft. Lewis, Wash., and 12 at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada.
   ---=
   Stand-alone military housing units at the following locations
were also recommended for closure, at a total savings of $4.9
million annually:
   CONNECTICUT: Manchester, Ansonia, Orange, Milford, Fairfield,
Westport, Shelton, New Britain, East Windsor, Portland, Plainville
and Middletown.
   ILLINOIS: Worth Family Housing (town not specified.)
   FLORIDA: USARC Addison Housing (town not specified.)
   MARYLAND: Washington-Baltimore NIKE site.
   MASSACHUSETTS: Burlington, Nahant, Wakefield, Beverly, Hull,
Randolph,
   Bedford, Swansea and Topsfield.
   MISSOURI: St. Louis Area Support Center Wherry Housing.
   NEW JERSEY: Four Nike base housing sites (towns not specified.)
   NEW YORK: Dry Hill Family Housing, Manhattan Beach Housing and
three Nike base housing sites (towns not specified.)
   PENNSYLVANIA: Irwin Support Detachment Annex, two Coraopolis
Family Housing sites and seven sites described as Pitt Family
Housing (locations not specified.)
   RHODE ISLAND: Family Housing Davisville and North Smithfield.
   VIRGINIA: Manassas, Norfolk and Woodbridge.
   WASHINGTON: Youngs Lake, Midway and Sun Prairie family housing
sites.
