<HEAD>Protesters Disrupt Oakland City Council Meeting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 70 protesters disrupted a City
Council meeting to denounce a proposed immigration service
detention center before police broke up the demonstration.
   The protesters were in the council chambers when members arrived
Tuesday night, and the meeting was recessed until about 20 police
officers led the demonstrators away.
