<SECOND>PM-Obit-Bond,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Character Actor David Bond Dies At 74</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Character actor David Bond, who appeared on
Broadway, in motion pictures and on some of the most popular TV
shows of the 1950s and '60s, has died at age 74 of complications
from leukemia.
   Born Alfred Allegro, Bond appeared on Broadway in ``Othello''
and ``Accidentally Yours'' before moving west in the 1940s to make
motion pictures.
   He was seen in such films as ``The Late George Apley,'' ``The
Private Affairs of Bel Ami,'' ``Joan of Arc,'' ``The Great
Caruso,'' ``Julius Caesar'' and ``House Calls.''
   His television credits included regular appearances on such
series as ``Dragnet,'' ``The Twilight Zone,'' ``Dobie Gillis'' and
``The Untouchables.''
   Bond died Sunday at Humana Hospital in West Hills.
