<HEAD>Man Charged With Murder in Deaths of Wife, Three Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was charged with murder after the
bodies of his wife and three children were found with their throats
slashed in their home, authorities said.
   The bodies of Nell Virginia Carter, 35, and her children,
Shameka Davis, 13, Natasha M. Carter, 8, and Lee Artis Carter Jr.,
7, were found early Tuesday by family members and police after Mrs.
Carter's brother became concerned that he could not contact her.
   Lee Artis Carter, 36, was jailed without bond. Carter, said by
neighbors to be the father of the two younger children, was first
taken to a hospital for cuts on his wrists caused by a razor blade,
fire department medics Chief T.L. Bryant said.
   Police would not comment on the wrist injuries.
   Neighbor Mark Carter said Mrs. Carter's brother, Bubba Davis,
had told him Lee Artis Carter would not let Davis in the house
Monday to see his sister.
   ``They had been trying to get in touch with her all day Sunday
and Monday,'' Mark Carter said Davis told him. ``He said she didn't
go to work Monday and the kids didn't go to school.
   ``The brother said they stayed in arguments a good bit. He said
he had told her if she ever left, he would kill her.''
   Mrs. Carter had worked for the state Department of Corrections
in an anti-drug program. Carter worked as a bagger at the Gunter
Air Force Base commissary.
