<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Demeter     04-19 0231</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Demeter,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gypsy Monarch Baron Demeter Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MULHOUSE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dominitchi Demeter, considered a king
among Gypsies, died at a hospital where hundreds of his followers
flocked upon hearing of his illness, police and hospital officials
said.
   Demeter, 57, was admitted last week to the Mulhouse Hospital
Center, suffering from cerebral congestion. He was in a coma when
he died Tuesday night, a hospital spokesman said.
   About 700 Romany Gypsies of Hungarian origin had gathered in the
Mulhouse region in eastern France when they heard that the Gypsy
leader, known as Baron Demeter, was ill. More than 100 caravans
were parked Wednesday at an unused mine in nearby Wittenheim.
   The hospital spokesman said hundreds of Gypsies filed through
the hospital over the last few days to pay respects to Demeter. A
special telephone line was installed to take care of phone calls by
followers in France and abroad inquiring about his condition, the
spokesman said on condition of anonymity.
   ``Baron Demeter had a considerable audience among the Gypsy
diaspora,'' said a police official, also speaking anonymously.
``The entire community, from all continents, was following the
agony of the patriarch.''
   A police spokesman said Demeter's body would be transported
Thursday to the Paris region, accompanied, in the Gypsy tradition,
by an all-male escort. The body was to be buried on Friday, but the
exact burial site was not immediately known.
</TEXT>
