<HEAD>London Shares Higher But Slipping At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange were
higher at midday Wednesday, but were slipping from the day's best
levels as the market's early rally ran out of steam.
   Shares advanced from the opening on the back of a strong
performance Tuesday in New York, where reassuring inflation news
and computerized program trading propelled the Dow Jones industrial
average to 2,379.40, a gain of 41.61 points, and its highest level
since the October 1987 crash.
   ``The buying appears to have dried up,'' said one British equity
salesman.
   Another London dealer said the market rose ``a bit too quickly
which killed off a lot of trade.''
   At about 12:15 p.m. in London, the Financial Times-Stock
Exchange 100-share index was 8.2 points, or 0.4 percent, higher at
2,082.6, near its morning low of 2,081.4. Its best level was
2,096.8.
   Volume amounted to a moderately healthy 435.3 million shares by
midday, compared with 272.9 million shares Tuesday.
