<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Dun&amp;Bradstreet     04-19 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Dun &amp; Bradstreet,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Posts 14.9 Percent in 1st-Qtr Profit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dun &amp; Bradstreet Corp., a leading marketer of
business information and services, said Wednesday its first-quarter
profit rose 14.9 percent to a record for the period on a 5.0
percent increase in revenue.
   The company said its earned $143.3 million, or 77 cents a share,
in the three months ended March 31 compared with $124.7 million, or
67 cents a share, a year earlier.
   First-quarter revenue rose to $1.06 billion from $1.01 billion a
year earlier.
   Among the company's products are the Donnelly Yellow Pages
operations, the Nielsen television audience ratings and Moody's
Investors Service credit ratings. Its business services are
marketed under the names McCormack &amp; Dodge, Dataquest and Petroleum
Information, among others.
