<FIRST>u f AM-Eastern-Food 1stLd-Writethru   04-19 0291</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Eastern-Food, 1st Ld-Writethru,0298</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coffee, Tea or Wage Concessions?</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Eastern-Lorenzo, Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: SUBS 2nd graf to ADD New York; picks up 3rd graf pvs bg'ng,
``As soon ...; ADDS byline</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARCY GORDON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Although Eastern Airlines has been on strike for
nearly seven weeks, some of its flight attendants still seem to be
serving.
   During the recent marathon negotiations in Washington and New
York between Eastern union officials and ex-baseball commissioner
Peter V. Ueberroth's team, flight attendant representatives seemed
to always get stuck ordering food, coffee and sodas for the group,
some participants in the talks said.
   ``As soon as somebody says `lunch', a flight attendant grabs a
pad and starts writing, taking orders,'' said one negotiator, who
asked not to be identified.
   Some union activists say the situation is typical of the
treatment accorded the flight attendants, who historically have
complained of discrimination. They are considered the easiest
employees to replace in an airline strike and therefore the least
powerful.
   The airline's flight attendants had reason to cheer Wednesday,
however, when they were told that they would be represented on the
Eastern creditors committee. Their union, the Transport Workers
Union, had been excluded from the creditors panel at the start of
Eastern's bankruptcy proceeding while their fellow pilots and
Machinists were represented.
   Mary Jane Barry, president of the Transport Workers local at
Eastern, will be the designated representative and will attend her
first committee meeting on Thursday, union sources said.
   The creditors committee also includes a representative of
non-union employees at Eastern, Mary Grace Shore. Her presence
irritated union officials, who allege that her group _ Positive
Employee Action Committee at Eastern, or PEACE _ is sponsored by
the airline's management.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
